I2AI_6 E4
The basic axiom to use here is the definition of conditional probability:
We have
\[
\begin{flalign}
P(A,B|e) = \frac{P(A,B,e)}{P(E)} &&
\end{flalign}
\]
and
\[
\begin{flalign}
P(A|B,e)P(B|e) = \frac{P(A,B,e)P(B,e)}{P(B,e)P(e)} = \frac{P(A,B,e)}{P(e)} &&
\end{flalign}
\]
hence
\[
\begin{flalign}
P(A,B|e) = P(A|B,e)P(B|e) &&
\end{flalign}
\]

I2AI_6 E5
Show that the statement of conditional independence
\[
\begin{flalign}
P(A,B|C)=P(A|C)P(B|C) &&
\end{flalign}
\]
is equivalent to each of the statements
\[
\begin{flalign}
P(A|B,C)=P(A|C) \quad \textrm{and} \quad P(B|A,C)=P(B|C) &&
\end{flalign}
\]

